en_68440_0	The United Nations General Assembly today elected the Permanent Representative of Sri Lanka, Ambassador Dr. Palitha Kohona, as Chair of the Sixth Committee, the top legal body of the General Assembly, for its 68th Session.
en_68440_1	Previously he had been overwhelmingly endorsed for the position by the Asia - Pacific Group.
en_68440_2	Dr. Kohona is the first Sri Lankan to be elected to chair the Sixth Committee of the General Assembly.
